{"lemma":"مُدْبِراً","slug":"مُدْبِراً","root":"د.ب.ر","root_slug":"د-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ب-ر","pos":"ADV","pos_camel":"adv","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُدْبِر","root":"دبر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":8},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12021","n12023","n12024"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%8B"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"active participle of دَبَّرَ (dabbara)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"designer, maker, arranger"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/mu.dab.bir/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12021","headword_ar":"مُدْبِرٌ","root":"dbx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Going, turning his back; turning back;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see its verb, 4]. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lahumo mino muqobilK","text_ar":"مَا لَهُمْ مِنْ مُقْبِلٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA mudobirK","text_ar":"وَلَا مُدْبِرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They have not one that goes forward nor one that goes back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) In the phrase in the Kur [ix. 25],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~a wal~ayotumo mudobiriyna","text_ar":"ثُمَّ وَلَّيْتُمْ مُدْبِرِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then ye turned back retreating"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the last word is a corroborative denotative of state; for with every"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawoliyap","text_ar":"تَوْلِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_idobaAr","text_ar":"اـِدْبَار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAbirN","text_ar":"دَابِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAbN mudobirN","text_ar":"نَابٌ مُدْبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to signify (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An aged she-camel whose goodness has gone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN mdbrpN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ مدبرةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudobirapN","text_ar":"مُدْبِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A land upon which rain has fallen partially, not generally,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not universally."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qbl","text_ar":"قبل"},{"kind":"text","text":". [This explanation is there given as though applying also to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArD mqblp","text_ar":"ارض مقبلة"},{"kind":"text","text":", app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqobilapN","text_ar":"مُقْبِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but I think that there is an omission, and that the latter phrase has the contr. meaning.])"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12023","headword_ar":"مُدَبَّرٌ","root":"dbx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A slave"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made to be free after his owner's death;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to whom his owner has said,"},{"kind":"text","text":"“"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art free after my death;"},{"kind":"text","text":"”"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose emancipation has been made to depend upon his owner's death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12024","headword_ar":"مُدَبِّرٌ","root":"dbx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[is extensively and variously applied as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who manages, conducts, orders,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regulates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"affairs of any kind, but generally affairs of importance]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA@lomadab~iraAti A^amorFA","text_ar":"فَا@لْمَدَبِّرَاتِ اَمْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lxxix. 5], signifies [accord. to most of the Expositors]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And those"},{"kind":"text","text":"angels"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who are charged with the managing, conducting, ordering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regulating, of affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also Bd.])"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%A8%D8%B1/","headword_ar":"مدبر","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23609#b7d8ab","body_html":"<span>المدبر: من أعتق عن دبر، فالمطلق منه: أن يعلق عتقه بموت مطلق، مثل: إن مت فأنت حر، أو بموت يكون الغالب وقوعه، مثل: إن مت إلى مائة سنة فأنت حر. والمقيد منه: أن يعلقه بموت مقيد، مثل: أن مت في مرضي هذا فأنت حر.</span>"}]}}